Race.SpecificTitle: PW Prop. No. 1 -- 2.07 Mills Renewal - PJ - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Parishwide Propositions
Proposition No. 1
(Health Unit Millage Renewal)
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of Grant, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), continue to levy a special tax of two and seven hundredths (2.07) mills on all property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $105,570 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2018 and ending with the year 2027, for the purpose of maintaining a Health Unit and other miscellaneous expenses incurred in the operation of this unit?

Race.SpecificTitle: PW Prop. No. 2 -- 3.22 Mills Renewal - PJ - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Parishwide Propositions
Proposition No. 2
(Courthouse & Jail Millage Renewal)
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of Grant, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), continue to levy a special tax of three and twenty-two hundredths (3.22) mills on all property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $164,220 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2018 and ending with the year 2027, for the purpose of maintaining the Parish Courthouse, all Courthouse Annex Buildings and Jail?

Race.SpecificTitle: PW Prop. No. 3 -- 8.61 Mills Renewal - PJ - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Parishwide Propositions
Proposition No. 3
(Roads & Bridges Millage Renewal)
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of Grant, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), continue to levy a special tax of eight and sixty-one hundredths (8.61) mills on all property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $439,110 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2018 and ending with the year 2027, for the purpose of constructing, improving, repairing and maintaining public roads and bridges, title to which shall be in the public?
